external_knowledge:
- 'Given consent' implies the participant has agreed to participate in the study;
- 'Funded by Pharmaceutical Company X' specifies the source of funding for the study;
- 'More than two sessions' indicates the participant has attended at least three sessions.

- 'Study 1' refers to a specific research study;
- 'Health condition' is synonymous with 'medical diagnosis';
- 'More than one participant' implies a count greater than 1.

- 'Digital addresses' refers to the email addresses of the participants;
- 'Wise souls' refers to participants who are older than 50 years;
- 'Embarked on the journey of Cognitive Behavioral Therapy' means the participants have taken part in sessions with the treatment plan 'Cognitive Behavioral Therapy';
- 'Given their consent to join the session' means the participants have a consent status of 'given'.

- 'study' is metaphorically referred to as a 'garden';
- 'participants' are metaphorically referred to as 'flowers';
- 'sessions' are metaphorically referred to as 'sunlight';
- The average age of participants can be thought of as the maturity level of the flowers in the garden;
- The number of participants can be thought of as the number of flowers in the garden.
